# Config.h diff — apply when switching to AMOLED-1.43

Apply the changes below to `src/Config.h` in the firmware tree. These
are the only Config changes needed; everything else (touch lock,
gear-shift thresholds, BLE intervals, screensaver behaviour) stays
the same so the user feel is identical across hardware variants.

```diff
--- a/src/Config.h
+++ b/src/Config.h
@@ display ---------------------------------------------
-  constexpr int      LCD_W            = 240;
-  constexpr int      LCD_H            = 240;
+  constexpr int      LCD_W            = 466;
+  constexpr int      LCD_H            = 466;
   constexpr uint32_t I2C_FREQ_HZ      = 400000;
   constexpr int      RENDER_FPS       = 60;
-  // 3D-printed bezel hides ~28px on top and bottom — keep important UI inside.
-  constexpr int      UI_SAFE_TOP      = 30;
-  constexpr int      UI_SAFE_BOTTOM   = LCD_H - 30;
+  // AMOLED has no bezel — but a round 466 px display has corners
+  // physically cut. Keep ~12% safe margin so text doesn't clip on
+  // the chord. (30/240 = 12.5% → 58/466 = 12.4%.)
+  constexpr int      UI_SAFE_TOP      = 58;
+  constexpr int      UI_SAFE_BOTTOM   = LCD_H - 58;

@@ brightness -----------------------------------------
-  constexpr uint8_t  BRIGHT_FULL      = 255;
-  constexpr uint8_t  BRIGHT_DIM       = 80;
+  // AMOLED 0x51 register is also 0-255 but the perceived brightness
+  // curve differs from LCD backlight. Cap at 200 for non-OLED-burn
+  // safety; user can dial up via Brightness screen if they really
+  // want full punch.
+  constexpr uint8_t  BRIGHT_FULL      = 200;
+  constexpr uint8_t  BRIGHT_DIM       = 60;

@@ build version --------------------------------------
-  constexpr const char* BUILD_VERSION = "v2.6.0";
+  constexpr const char* BUILD_VERSION = "v2.6.0-amoled";
```

## What stays the same

- All gear-shift logic (dwell, dead-band, hysteresis, gyro-intent gate)
- All BLE service UUIDs, characteristic layout, MTU, conn params
- Calibration thresholds
- Touch lock timing
- Screensaver wake-on-motion
- WiFi STA config
- OTA partition layout (partitions.csv unchanged — same 16 MB flash)

## What to expect at boot

- Splash renders sharp at 466×466 (vector logo scales fine; bitmap
  splash assets will look softer — re-export at 466 if you want
  pixel-perfect)
- Boot zero IMU sequence: identical (QMI8658 same as before)
- BLE pair: identical
- Gear digit centre will look ~1.94× larger in physical size — may
  feel almost too bold; we'll tune the digit font size in a follow-up
  patch once you've seen it on hardware

## Arduino IDE settings — required change

```
PSRAM:  "OPI PSRAM"      (← changed from "QSPI PSRAM")
```

Everything else (Board, USB Mode, Flash Size 16MB, Partition,
LoopCore, EventsCore) stays the same as the LCD-1.28 build.
